<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFFD882E30DD31D37DDFF8D2" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFFD882E30DD31D37DDFF8D2" blockId="9.[151,1437,1473,2041]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFD882E30DD31D37E6AFA4A" bold="true" box="[151,266,1473,1500]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFD882E315631D37E00FA4A" bold="true" box="[284,352,1473,1500]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Adult</emphasis>
. Vertex subrectangular, base straight, dorsally completely flattened including area adjacent to median ocellus, bearing distinct anteorbital tubercle; separated from genae by transverse suture; genal processes lying in the same plane as vertex, flattened dorsally, usually irregularly truncate apically. Antenna shorter than twice head width; segment 3 longest. Rostrum short, hardly visible in profile. Metatibia lacking genual spine, with 4â€“6 sclerotised, relatively evenly spaced apical spurs. Forewing rhomboidal, subrectangular or broadly, evenly rounded apically, usually with flattened, slightly widened vein C+Sc. Hindwing with vein M+Cu. Male proctiger unipartite, tubular. Male subgenital plate hemisphaerical. Paramere lamellar, simple. Distal segment of aedeagus simple, with weak oval apical dilatation; sclerotised end tube of ductus ejaculatorius short and thick, almost straight. Female terminalia cuneate, short; circumanal ring cruciform. 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFD882E32A732F37C91F96A" bold="true" box="[749,1009,1761,1788]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fifth instar immature</emphasis>
. Antenna 8-segmented. Capitate setae absent. Additional pore fields present as 1+1 convoluted loops. Following numbers of marginal sectasetae present: hindwing pads 0+0 or 1+1, abdomen 3+3 or 4+4.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFFD882E308D335F7DC7F826" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFFD882E308D335F7C87F8FE" blockId="9.[151,1437,1473,2041]" box="[199,999,1869,1896]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFD882E308D335F7E31F8FE" bold="true" box="[199,337,1869,1896]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Description</emphasis>
of adults and immatures by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFFD882E32DA335C7C5FF8FE" author="Capener, A. L." box="[656,831,1870,1896]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="37 - 61" refId="ref70143" refString="Capener, A. L. (1973) Southern African Psyllidae (Homoptera). 3. A new genus and new species of South African Psyllidae. Journal of the Entomological Society of Southern Africa, 36, 37 - 61." type="journal article" year="1973">Capener (1973)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFFD882E333C335C7C82F8FE" author="Li, F." box="[886,994,1870,1896]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refId="ref70850" refString="Li, F. (2011) Psyllidomorpha of China (Insecta: Hemiptera). Science Press, Beijing, XLI + 1976 pp." type="book" year="2011">Li (2011)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFFD882E308D33607DC7F826" blockId="9.[151,1437,1473,2041]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFD882E308D33607F9DF81A" bold="true" box="[199,253,1906,1932]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Egg.</emphasis>
Oblong oval, slightly curved, 3â€“4 times as long as wide; irregularly narrowing at apex which is subacute (
<figureCitation id="136B2A26FFFD882E30EA33847F94F826" box="[160,244,1942,1968]" captionStart="FIGURES 22â€“26" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1290,1315]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,445,1268]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,445,1271]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 22â€“26. Eggs of psyllids associated with Detarieae; 22, Apsyllopsis mexicana; 23, Colophorina guarani sp. nov.; 24, Platycorypha amazonica sp. nov.; 25, Jataiba uncigera sp. nov.; 26, Mitrapsylla sp.â€”Scales 0.2 mm; 24â€“26 = scale 26." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3669655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3669655/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
). Surface with cellular microsculpture.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFFD882D308D33AB7E0DFD12" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFFD882D308D33AB7AFAFED4" blockId="9.[151,1437,1473,2041]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1437,153,644]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFD882E308D33AB7E2FF842" bold="true" box="[199,335,1977,2004]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFFD882E311233A87E87F842" box="[344,487,1978,2004]" class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" genus="Colophorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFD882E311233A87E87F842" box="[344,487,1978,2004]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Colophorina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as diagnosed above, is a pantropical genus closest related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFFD882E34E433A97AFDF842" authority="Aulmann." authorityName="Aulmann." box="[1198,1437,1978,2004]" class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" genus="Euryconus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFD882E34E433A97A46F842" box="[1198,1318,1979,2004]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Euryconus</emphasis>
Aulmann.
</taxonomicName>
Species of both share the same head structure and are associated with Leguminosae. 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFFD882E341233CC7B87F86E" box="[1112,1255,2014,2040]" class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" genus="Colophorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFD882E341233CC7B87F86E" box="[1112,1255,2014,2040]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Colophorina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes 10 de- scribed species (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFFE882D3107348B7EC7FF25" author="Li, F." box="[333,423,153,179]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refId="ref70850" refString="Li, F. (2011) Psyllidomorpha of China (Insecta: Hemiptera). Science Press, Beijing, XLI + 1976 pp." type="book" year="2011">Li 2011</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFFE882D31F8348B7D2FFF25" author="Ouvrard, D." box="[434,591,153,179]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refId="ref71416" refString="Ouvrard, D. (2019) Psyl'list-The World Psylloidea Database. Available from: https: // www. hemiptera-databases. org / psyllist /? &amp; lang = en (accessed 20 November 2019)" type="url" year="2019">Ouvrard 2019</bibRefCitation>
) but several species currently misplaced in 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFFE882D347A348B7A77FF25" authority="Schwarz" authorityName="Schwarz" authorityYear="1904" box="[1072,1303,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" genus="Euphalerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFE882D347A348B7BD1FF25" box="[1072,1201,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Euphalerus</emphasis>
Schwarz
</taxonomicName>
also belong here (D. Burckhardt, unpublished data). On the other hand, the only Neotropical member, 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFFE882D34C634AF7E54FF6D" authority="(Brown &amp; Hodkinson, 1988)" authorityName="Burckhardt &amp; Queiroz" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Burckhardt &amp; Queiroz" baseAuthorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" genus="Epiacizzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="favis">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFE882D34C634AF7B82FF41" box="[1164,1250,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">C. favis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFFE882D34BB34AF7E4CFF6D" author="Brown, R. G. &amp; Hodkinson, I. D." pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refId="ref69240" refString="Brown, R. G. &amp; Hodkinson, I. D. (1988) Taxonomy and ecology of the jumping plant-lice of Panama (Homoptera: Psylloidea). E. J. Brill, Scandinavian Science Press Ltd., Leiden, New York, Kopenhagen, Koln, 304 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 156853988 X 00241" type="book" year="1988">Brown &amp; Hodkinson, 1988</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, does not conform with the diagnosis provided above. It is not congeneric with 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFFE882D34F534F37A52FF6C" authorityName="Capener" authorityYear="1973" box="[1215,1330,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" genus="Colophorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cassiae">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFE882D34F534F37A52FF6C" box="[1215,1330,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">C. cassiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus id="54EB8801FFFE882D352634F37AFCFF6D" box="[1388,1436,225,251]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">type</typeStatus>
species of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFFE882D317D35167EA6FE88" box="[311,454,260,286]" class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" genus="Colophorina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFE882D317D35167EA6FE88" box="[311,454,260,286]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Colophorina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but with 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFFE882D327D35177DBEFE88" authority="Li" authorityName="Li" box="[567,734,260,286]" class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" genus="Euphalerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="edentalis">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFE882D327D35177DDCFE88" box="[567,700,260,286]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">E. edentalis</emphasis>
Li
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus id="54EB8801FFFE882D335935177C23FE89" box="[787,835,261,287]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFFE882D338A35177B35FE88" authority="Li" authorityName="Li" authorityYear="2002" box="[960,1109,260,286]" class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" genus="Epiacizzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFE882D338A35177B55FE88" box="[960,1077,261,286]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Epiacizzia</emphasis>
Li
</taxonomicName>
(D. Burckhardt, unpublished data) to which it is transferred here as 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFFE882D320E353B7B22FED4" authority="(Brown &amp; Hodkinson, 1988)" authorityName="Burckhardt &amp; Queiroz" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Burckhardt &amp; Queiroz" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[580,1090,296,322]" class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" genus="Epiacizzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="favis" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFE882D320E353B7D95FED4" box="[580,757,296,322]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Epiacizzia favis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFFE882D334E353A7B59FED4" author="Brown, R. G. &amp; Hodkinson, I. D." box="[772,1081,296,322]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refId="ref69240" refString="Brown, R. G. &amp; Hodkinson, I. D. (1988) Taxonomy and ecology of the jumping plant-lice of Panama (Homoptera: Psylloidea). E. J. Brill, Scandinavian Science Press Ltd., Leiden, New York, Kopenhagen, Koln, 304 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 156853988 X 00241" type="book" year="1988">Brown &amp; Hodkinson, 1988</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFE882D3407353A7BAEFED4" bold="true" box="[1101,1230,296,322]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21757CAFFFE882D3407353A7BAEFED4" box="[1101,1230,296,322]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
